Plateau State Governor, Simon Lalong, has advised Nigerians not to undermine sporting activities in the society, saying it is a powerful instrument of building peace and unity. Lalong. Photo/FACEBOOK/PLSGov/  Earlier in his remarks, Commander of OPSH, General Ali, who thanked God for witnessing the New Year, said the Chief of Defence Staff organised the football competition and peace and unity marathon through the OPSH, but physically carried out by the sector commanders, who are closer to the people at the grassroots.
  
Ali said the OPSH, which is permanently stationed in Jos as its headquarters, also comprises parts of Bauchi and Kaduna states, adding that the competition is aimed at solidifying the peace already achieved.  At the end of the competition, Barkin Ladi emerged first, followed by Riyom, while Shendam came third. Different prizes, trophies and cash were presented to the three best teams, while consolation prizes were given to other competitors.